    <refsection id="Description_MATPINV">
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
            The MATPINV Block outputs the inverse of a non square input matrix using the SVD theory.
            if the SVD decomposition of A is equal to:
        </para>
        <para>A=USV'</para>
        <para>The pseudoinverse X of A is given by:</para>
        <para>
            X=VS"U' where S"(i,j)=1/S(i,j) (if S(i,j)Â =0), U' and V are respectively the transpose of U and V'.
        </para>
        <para>
            and we have A*X*A=A and X*A*X=X. Both A*X and X*A are Hermitian. A warning message is printed if
            the input is badly scaled or nearly singular.
        </para>
        <para>
            When the input is a MxN matrix the output is a NxM matrix.
        </para>
        <para>
            The equivalent function of this block in Scilab is <link linkend="pinv">pinv</link>.
        </para>
    </refsection>
